A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Subpart 2 of Part 1 of Article 16 of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of
2 Georgia Annotated, relating to compulsory attendance for students in elementary and
3 secondary education, so as to provide that student performers shall not be counted absent
4 from school due to performing in certain productions, subject to certain conditions, for no
5 more than all or part of 25 school days; to provide that the instruction and related services
6 provided by a studio teacher to a student performer are aligned with the curriculum and
7 content standards being delivered at the student performer's school under certain
8 circumstances; to provide for performance certification forms and certification; to authorize
9 the Department of Labor, in consultation with the Department of Education, to develop such
10 certification forms and promulgate rules and regulations; to provide for authorizations by
11 parents or guardians relating to the education records of student performers; to provide for
12 definitions; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
