14 SECTION 1.
15 Subpart 2 of Part 1 of Article 16 of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia
16 Annotated, relating to compulsory attendance for students in elementary and secondary
17 education, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
18 "20-2-692.4.
19 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
20 (1) 'Child labor coordinator' means the person who is designated by the employing unit
21 as responsible for the coordination and safety of the student performer, including, but not
22 limited to, ensuring that the student performer is provided instruction and related services
23 by a studio teacher.
24 (2) 'Employing unit' means the person, agency, association, company, corporation,
25 group, or other organization using the services of a student performer.
26 (3) 'Performance' or 'performing' means participation in a production that is available to
27 the public, will be made available to the public, or is intended to be made available to the
28 public.
29 (4) 'Production' means a work that is being presented, will be presented, or is intended
30 to be presented by way of, but not limited to, the following: stage, screen, television,
31 internet, digital recording, video tape, audio tape, still photographic or phonographic
32 recording of any kind, open air, or runway modeling. A production shall include an
33 exhibition, as defined by the Department of Labor, but shall not include any participation
34 or performance related to a production or exhibition produced exclusively by a public
35 school, private school, or religious organization if such public school, private school, or
36 religious organization has not been issued a current employing unit certification by the
37 Department of Labor.
38 (5) 'Student performer' means a person under 18 years of age who is enrolled in a public
39 pre-kindergarten program or elementary or secondary school located in this state, who
40 has been issued a current minor's certification by the Department of Labor or current
